## SVELTE 5 RUNES

### $state
```
let x = $state(0);              // reactive
let obj = $state({...});         // deep proxy
let raw = $state.raw({...});     // no proxy — large objects, API responses
$state.snapshot(proxy);          // for external APIs (structuredClone etc)
$state.eager(val);               // immediate UI feedback on user action (sparingly)
```
- Only `$state` for values causing UI updates. Use `$state.raw` for reassign-only data. Arrow functions for class methods as handlers. Don't destructure proxies (refs evaluate at destructure time).

### $derived
```
let d = $derived(expr);          // simple
let d = $derived.by(() => {...}); // complex
let {a,b} = $derived(stuff());   // destructured = reactive
```
- ALWAYS use `$derived` not `$effect` for computed values. Writable since 5.25 (optimistic UI). Side-effect free. Push-pull reactivity skips referentially identical values.

### $effect
```
$effect(() => { /* after mount, re-runs on tracked state */ return () => { /* teardown */ }; });
$effect.pre(() => { /* before DOM update */ });
$effect.tracking();    // am I in a tracking context?
$effect.pending();     // pending async count in boundary
```
- ESCAPE HATCH — avoid. Never update `$state` inside. For D3/GSAP/Three.js prefer `{@attach}`. For window/doc events use `<svelte:window>`/`<svelte:document>`. For debug use `$inspect`. Values after `await`/`setTimeout` NOT tracked.

### $props
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  interface Props { title: string; onClose: () => void; children?: Snippet; }
  let { title, onClose, children }: Props = $props();
  const uid = $props.id();  // unique, SSR-stable (5.20+)
</script>
```
- Always type with interface. Props-dependent values use `$derived`. Don't mutate props. `$props.id()` for label/aria linking.

### Built-ins (no install)
```ts
import { SvelteMap, SvelteSet, SvelteURL, SvelteDate, MediaQuery, createSubscriber } from 'svelte/reactivity';
import { innerWidth, scrollY, online, devicePixelRatio } from 'svelte/reactivity/window';
import { createContext } from 'svelte';           // 5.40+ — replaces set/getContext
import { hydratable } from 'svelte';              // 5.36+ — avoid re-fetching on hydration
import { fork } from 'svelte';                    // 5.42+ — preload async work
```

### {@attach} (5.29+)
```svelte
<div {@attach myAttachment}>
<button {@attach tooltip(content)}>
<div {@attach enabled && conditional}>
<div {@attach fromAction(legacyAction, () => arg)}>  <!-- convert actions -->
```
- Fully reactive (re-runs on state change). Prefer over `use:action`. On components → Symbol prop (spread to receive). For expensive setup, pass getter + child `$effect`.

### Async (5.36+, experimental)
- Enable: `compilerOptions.experimental.async: true`
- `await` in `<script>`, `$derived`, markup. Wrap in `<svelte:boundary pending={snippet}>`. Updates synchronized. `$effect.pending()` for loading. Stable in Svelte 6.

### Snippets & Events
```svelte
{#snippet greeting(name)}<p>hello {name}!</p>{/snippet}
{@render greeting('world')}
{@render children?.()}
<button onclick={handler}>   <!-- or {onclick} shorthand -->
<svelte:window onkeydown={handler} />
```
- Keyed `{#each}` always: `(item.id)`. Never use index as key.

## REMOTE FUNCTIONS (default for internal flows)
From `$app/server` in `.remote.ts`:
- `query` → reads (cached, `.refresh()`) · `query.batch` → N+1 solution
- `form` → submissions (spread onto `<form>`, progressive enhancement) · `command` → mutations (event handlers only, no render)
- `prerender` → build-time static data (CDN-cached)

Rules: Validate all input w/ Valibot schema · `getRequestEvent()` for cookies · Single-flight: `getPosts().refresh()` inside handlers · `requested()` + `refreshAll()` for client-driven refreshes · `form.fields.x.as('text')` for attrs · `form.validate()` / `form.preflight(schema)` · `invalid(issue.x('msg'))` for server errors · `_` prefix for sensitive fields · `command` can't redirect

